# Auth & RBAC Guardian

Security and privacy playbook for identity and course roles.

## Auth

- Production: CWL SAML via `passport-ubcshib`
- Dev: local fake users when `SAML_AVAILABLE=false`
- Session: `engeai.sid`, httpOnly, sameSite lax, secure in production

## RBAC

- Affiliations: student, faculty, staff, empty — staff/empty blocked appropriately
- Page gates: `validateCourseAccess`, `requireInstructorForCourse`, `requireStudentForCourse`
- API gates: `requireInstructorForCourseAPI`, `requireStudentForCourseAPI`, `requireInstructorGlobal`
- Platform admin: `GlobalUser.isAdmin` — env PUID seeds; admins bypass instructor checks

## Privacy

- Monitor: instructor-only; conversation exports/downloads — minimum necessary data
- Never expose student PUID in UI/APIs where roster policy forbids
- Flag content: handle harassment/inappropriate categories per product rules

## Defense in depth

- Monitor API routes should use instructor API middleware, not page gating alone
- New export/backup endpoints: high risk — Red Team required in handoff

